# Localization Rules (uiText.xls)

- **All UI text must come from localization**: use `GameEntry.Localization.GetString("<id>")` (numeric id keys).
- **ID policy**: Keep new ids within **< 100** when feasible; avoid introducing `20000+` ids.
- **No long-term English fallback**: If any non-English cell is blank/`<NoKey>`/whitespace, it must be **translated and filled**, not replaced by English.
- **When code introduces new text**:
  - Add a new row in `Doc/Language/uiText.xls` (or reuse an existing row if English is identical).
  - Fill **all language columns** (including Indonesian with local-friendly wording).
  - Remove/merge duplicated rows (same English meaning; ignore trailing `:`/`：`).
  - Update all code references to the final merged id(s).
- **Only fill missing**: Never overwrite an existing non-empty translation unless explicitly requested.

